{{Infobox university |name = Bolivia Adventist University |native_name = Universidad Adventista de Bolivia |image = |caption = |latin_name = |motto = |mottoeng = |established = 1931 |closed = |type = |affiliation = [[Seventh-day Adventist Church]] |endowment = |officer_in_charge = |chairman = Roberto O. Gullon |chancellor = |president = Mateo Salvador |vice-president = |superintendent = |provost = |vice_chancellor = |rector = |principal = |dean = |director = |head_label = |head = |faculty = |staff = |students = |undergrad = |postgrad = |doctoral = |other = |city = [[Cochabamba]] |state = |province = |country = [[Bolivia]] |coor = |campus = |former_names = |free_label = |free = |sports = |colors = |colours = |nickname = |mascot = |athletics = |affiliations = |website = [http://www.uab.edu.bo/ www.uab.edu.bo] |logo = |footnotes = }} '''Bolivia Adventist University''' ({{lang-es|Universidad Adventista de Bolivia}}), or '''UAB''', is a private [[coeducational]] [[Christian]] [[university]] in the city of [[Cochabamba]], the third-largest city in [[Bolivia]]. The university is affiliated to the [[Seventh-day Adventist Church]] and offers degrees in six major fields: [[Theology]], [[Health Sciences]], [[Nursing]], [[Education]], Economic and Administrative Sciences ([[Business]], etc.), and [[Engineering]]. UAB is the only Adventist university in Bolivia, but is one of ten such establishments in [[South America]].
